---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Starting with UNDER in Scrabble"
  description="Complete list of valid UNDER- words in Scrabble sorted by length. Strategy for extending prefix words to hit premium squares and score big with UNDER."
  keywords="under words scrabble, words starting with under, under prefix scrabble, underpin scrabble, underdog scrabble, scrabble under words list, prefix words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Starting with UNDER in Scrabble",
    "description": "Complete list of valid UNDER- words in Scrabble with strategy for using prefix extensions to hit premium squares.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-20",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-starting-with-under" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many words starting with UNDER are valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are approximately 200+ valid UNDER- words across both the TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS dictionaries. These range from 5 letters (UNDER itself is a valid standalone word worth 6 points) up to 13+ letters. SOWPODS contains additional UNDER- words not found in TWL." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best UNDER words for scoring in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The highest-scoring common UNDER words include UNDERJAW (18 points base), UNDERFIX (19 points base), and UNDERSIZE (19 points). For practical bingo scoring, 7-letter UNDER words like UNDERGO (9+50), UNDERPIN (11+50), and UNDERBID (11+50) are most valuable since they earn the 50-point bonus." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can UNDER be played as a word by itself in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! UNDER is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS as a standalone word worth 6 points. It functions as an adverb, adjective, and preposition. This makes it a useful short play early in the game, and even better as a setup for extending into longer UNDER- compound words on subsequent turns." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/letter-guides/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Letter Guides</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Starting with UNDER in Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-20">June 20, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        UNDER is one of Scrabble's most versatile prefixes — it attaches to hundreds of root words and creates plays that frequently reach bingo length. Unlike many prefixes, UNDER itself is a valid standalone word (6 points), giving you a foundation to build from on subsequent turns. This guide covers the most useful UNDER words by length, plus strategies for turning these compound words into premium-square dominators.
      </p>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">200+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid UNDER Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highest Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Score (7-letter)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5–13</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter Range</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card Grid: Most Useful UNDER Words -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 Best for Bingos</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDERGO (7) · UNDERBID (8) · UNDERPIN (8) · UNDERCUT (8) · UNDERDOG (8)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Highest Scoring</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDERJAW (18) · UNDERFIX (19) · UNDERPAY (14) · UNDERSKY (16) · UNDERBUY (13)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📝 Most Common</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDERSTAND · UNDERLINE · UNDERMINE · UNDERTAKE · UNDERWORLD · UNDERGO</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 Easy to Build</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDER · UNDERGO · UNDERDO · UNDONE · UNDERPIN · UNDERSEA · UNDERLIE</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">UNDER Words by Length (5–6 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Short UNDER words are your bread and butter. UNDER itself is only 5 letters and scores 6 points — modest but valid. The real value is playing UNDER early and extending it later, or finding 6-letter UNDER words that fit tight board spaces.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">5 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDER (6pts) — valid standalone in both TWL and SOWPODS</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">6 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDONE (7pts) · UNDERS (7pts) · UNDERM (SOWPODS)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Bingo-Length UNDER Words (7 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Seven-letter UNDER words are your bingo targets. With 5 letters locked into the prefix, you only need 2 more letters to complete a play — and the 50-point bonus is worth holding onto U-N-D-E-R if you spot an extension opportunity.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">7-Letter Bingos (common)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDERGO (9+50) · UNDERDO (9+50) · UNDERBID · UNDERLIE · UNDERSEA · UNDERFED · UNDERRAN · UNDERSET · UNDERPIN</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Since UNDER uses 5 of your 7 tiles, you only need <span class="text-white font-medium">2 compatible letters</span> to complete a bingo. Letters like G+O (UNDERGO), D+O (UNDERDO), or S+EA (UNDERSEA) finish the word. Hold the UNDER combo when your remaining tiles look promising.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">UNDER Words (8+ Letters)</h2>

      <p>Eight-letter and longer UNDER words are typically played as extensions — adding UNDER before an existing word on the board, or extending an UNDER word you played earlier. These are devastating when they land across premium squares.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">8 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDERBID · UNDERCUT · UNDERDOG · UNDERFED · UNDERPIN · UNDERLAY · UNDERLET · UNDERRUN · UNDERTOW · UNDERWAY</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">9 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDERMINE · UNDERLINE · UNDERPAID · UNDERSIGN · UNDERTAKE · UNDERTONE · UNDERSIDE · UNDERFOOT · UNDERDONE</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">10+ Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">UNDERSTAND · UNDERNEATH · UNDERTAKER · UNDERWORLD · UNDERSTATE · UNDERSCORE · UNDERCOVER · UNDERCROFT</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Prefix Extensions for Premium Squares</h2>

      <p>UNDER words are natural candidates for extension plays — adding your prefix to words already on the board. This strategy lets you play 8–10 letter words using only 5 tiles from your rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play UNDER early, extend later:</span> Drop UNDER on your first or second turn in a position where the word can be extended. If someone plays CUT later and it aligns, you can form UNDERCUT for massive points. Even adding S to make UNDERS keeps options open.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Front-hook existing words:</span> Scan the board for words like DOG, BID, CUT, FED, PIN, PAY, WAY, TOW, AGE, LINE. Adding UNDER in front creates valid plays. You only need 5 tiles to turn a 3-letter word into an 8-letter monster.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Reach Triple Word squares:</span> UNDER words at 8+ letters easily span the distance from center to edge TW squares. UNDERDOG starting at column 4 reaches TW at column 1 — tripling the entire word. That is 8×3 + 50 = 74+ points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Double-up with parallel plays:</span> When you play UNDER extending DOG into UNDERDOG, check if any of the perpendicular letters form valid cross-words. Each cross-word adds its full score — a well-placed extension with 3 cross-words can score 100+ points.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">UNDER vs Other Prefixes</h2>

      <p>How does UNDER compare to other common Scrabble prefixes? Here is a quick comparison to help you decide which prefix to prioritize when building your rack strategy.</p>

      <!-- Comparison Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ UNDER Advantages</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid standalone word (6pts). 200+ extensions. Common tiles (U,N,D,E,R). Works as both prefix and front-hook. Many 7-letter bingos available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ UNDER Drawbacks</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Uses 5 tiles for prefix alone (only 2 left for extension). U is uncommon in racks. No high-value letters in the prefix itself (all 1-2pt tiles). Requires board setup for best plays.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Rack Management Tip</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Holding U-N-D-E-R ties up 5 of your 7 tiles. Only commit to this if the board has <span class="text-white font-medium">clear extension targets</span> (existing words you can prefix). If no targets exist after 2 turns, break up the combo and play individual tiles for points instead.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-starting-with-trans/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Starting with TRANS in Scrabble</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-7-letter-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best 7-Letter Scrabble Words for Bingo Bonus</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-parallel-plays/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Parallel Plays: Score Big with Side-by-Side Words</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try these words in our free Scrabble solver — instant results, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
